#1.	Write a program which takes a tuple as an input and remove the first and last element from the tuple.And returns a tuple as an output. (hint: convert the tuple into a list)
A=(1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9)
print(type(A))
lis = list(A)
lis.pop(-1)
lis.pop(0)

A = tuple(lis)

